content: Generation--Semantic Extraction. List with commas between terms.

’Twas brillig, and the slithy toves
   Did gyre and gimble in the wabe;
All mimsy were the borogoves,
   And the mome raths outgrabe.

“Beware the Jabberwock, my son
   The jaws that bite, the claws that catch!
Beware the Jubjub bird, and shun
   The frumious Bandersnatch!”

Pull out all the made-up, nonsense words in the above passage and list them with commas between them.

chosen:
'Twas, brillig, and, the, slithy, toves
  ,Did, gyre, and, gimble, in, the, wabe;
All, mimsy, were, the, borogoves,,
  And, the, mome, raths, outgrabe.

“Beware, the, Jabberwock, my, son
  The, jaws, that, bite, the, claws, that, catch!
Beware, the, Jubjub, bird, and, shun
  The, frumious, Bandersnatch!”
rejected: 'Twas, brillig, semicolon, and toves, Did, gyre, and, gimble, in, the, wabe; All, mimsy, were, the, borogoves, And, the, mome, raths, outgrabe.
